GAN\nCompany, Inc.\nEverything in the Paint Line\n421 Tenth St. N. W. Nat. 7889\nThe National Dotty\nmost extensive preparations to\ntake advantage of Just such a situ\nation. Summer bargain sales have\nbeen arranged for and will be\npushed. Quick turnovers with\nsmall profits is the general plan.\nThe public generally always\nbenefits by such a condition while\nthe cash returns to the merchants,\nbeing Immediate, allow them to\nkeep the wheels turning all along\nthe line.\nBuyers Benefit\nBecause of the lack of buying\npower in recent weeks many mer\nchants had accumulated big\nstocks, but it now appears that\nthese will be assimilated during\nthe coming weeks. The consumer\nbenefits because prices have been\nmaterially reduced. According to\nbusiness leaders, almost every\nline has shown a decrease in\nprices, which must now make each\nline appeal generally to the buy\ning public.\nThis is especially noticeable in\nthe food products line. Most lines,\nespecially those which are brought\nfrom the farm, are lower than in\nrecent months. The housewife\nbenefits here, whatever the result\nto the producer himself.\nDepartment stores which have\nbeen hard pressed to enlarge\nsales during the past six or eight\nweeks now see signs of increasing\ndemands. It is anticipated by\nthem that the coming month will\nsee enough of an increase in\npurchasing to make certain a\nprosperous late summer and early\nautumn. And they are accepted as\nreflecting what may be looked for\nin all other lines of industry and\ntrade.\ni Huckleberries Supply moderate.\nSouthern, per quart. 15029e.\nI Lettuce\u2014One California, three New\nYork arrived; 21 cars trajk. tnrlnding\ni broken. New York express receipts\nlight; supply moderate, demand and\ntrading light, market dull. California\ncrates Iceberg. 4-\u00bb dozen, fair condition,\nbest *3.5*0 4; very few higher; poorer.\n*1.5*03. New York, 2-doxen crates,\nBig Boston, 75@9*C, few 11.\nLima Beans\u2014X uppl i ea moderate.\nSouthern, bu. hampets. *1.2502.88.\nOnions \u2014No car-lot arrivals, 1 reeon\naigned, S cars on track including\nbroken. Eastern Shore Virginia boat\nreceipts light. Supplies moderate; de\nmand slow; market very dull. Standard\ncrates. Yellow Bermudas. Texas. 11. S.\nCommer. wasty. *1**01.25. California,\nf. X. Is. few wasty 11.50. Eastern Shore\nVirginia, bu. hampers. Yellows, un-\nI graded, 75090 c; few higher.\nPeaches\u2014Three Georgia arrived; 12\ncars on track including broken. North\nCarolina truck and express receipt*\nlight. Supplies moderate, demand\nmoderate; market steady. Georgia. H-\nI bu. baskets, Hlleys. U. S. Is. 1S inches\nI min., mostly *1.25; 1% inches min..\n*1.50 01.85; Sa. Hileya, U. 8. Is. large\nsize. 13 00; few higher, small site 12.25;\nNorth Carolina. Ss, Hlleys. U. S. la.\nlarge alee, *3.2503.50; bu. baskets.\nHlleys, 1% min., *3.0f1; few higher.\nPeas\u2014Supplies moderate. California,\nhu. hampers. Telephones, |2.28e2.50;\nNew York, bu. baskets. Telephones,\n11.50\u00a9 2.00.\nPeppers\u2014Supplies light. Florida and\nNorth Carolina, bu. hampers, fancy\n*1.2501.50. Florida, pepper crates, fancy\n*2.2502.50; few \u00bbB.n*.\nPotatoes\u2014One Maine arrived. Re\nceipts equivalent to 9 Virginia. Norfolk\nand Hampton, 4 Western Shore Vir\nginia. 1 Eastern Shore Maryland, by\nboat. New stock, no cars on track.\nSupplies moderate: demand moderate;\nmarket about steady. All sections, stave\nbarrels. Cobblers, V. S. Is. best mostly\n93.25; poorer *.0*03.10; heated *2.250\n2.50. Eastern Shore Virginia, stave\nbarrels, Cobblers, culls 11.4001. 50. Old\nslock. 2 cars on track including broken\nSupplies light, demand limited; market\ndull. Maine. 100-lb. sacks. Mts., U. S.\nf Is. *2.0002.25; mostly *2.13.\nRaspberries\u2014Supplies moderate. East\nern Shore Maryland and nearby Ked.\nper pl.. 12\u00a9>lSc. Nearby black, per\nqt.. ISWUe.\nSquash\u2014Supplies moderate. Nearby\n',i-bti. hampers. 25030 c.\nTomatoes \u2014One Tennessee arrived; 8\ncars on track including broken. Re\nceipts equivalent to 1 car Western\nShore Virginia boat. Supplies light; de\nmand slow; market dull. Tennessee.\nI lugs, turning and ripes, wrapped. Bxs\nand larger. *1.7501.90. Western Shore\nVirginia, ss, green, unwrapped. un\ngraded. 75c\u00a9*l.\u00abn. Nearby *e-bu.\nhampers, npe *1.2501.50.\nWatermelons\u2014Seven Florida. 4 Georgia.\n1 South Carolina arrived; 15 recon\nsigned: 118 cars on track including\nbroken Supplies liberal: demand\nmoderate; market dull. Florida and\nGeorgia. Tom Watsons. 30-32 lb. avar\ni age. 35040 c: few higher, 78-2* lb.\naverage. 25030 c; 22-24 lb. average, 200\n25c: each. Car-lot sales. Georgik and\nFlorida, some sunburned and spotted.\nAll cars sold for freight and less.\nI IHI lAM/iTEURI\nJT nite\n.TV TONITE\na lANoy\nI I I I |1 PAVILIONS JUUMWC\nMoney Can\u2019t Juy Better Teeth\nPLATES *lO, *ls. AND *2O\nPlates Repaired While You Wait\nAll Work Done in My Own Labora\ntories\u2014No Long Waiting\u2014No\nHigh Prices\nCrown and Bridge Work\n$5 irnjofl $5\nEXTRACTIONS *I.OO\u2014BT GAS F\u2019.OO\nDR. SMATHERS\nRental Specialist\n027 SEVENTH ST. N. W.\nAcross from Gnldenberg's and Over\nPeople\u2019s Drug Store\nHours 9a.m.tn\u00df p. m. ME. 88.98\nSATURDAY, JULY 5, l\u00a93o\nEUROPEAN FIRM\nPLANS UTILin.\nEXPANSION\nPublic Utility Holding Takes\n35 Per Cent Interest in New\nLuxembougr Company\nAnnouncement was made yester\nday by F. 8. Burroughs, president\nof Public Utility Holding Corpora\ntion of America, that his company\nhas acquired a 35 per cent inter\nest in the Compagnie Grand d\u2019Elec\ntriclte du Luxembourg, a con\nstruction and distributing com\npany which is now undertaking\nthe electrification of the Grand\nDuchy of Luxembourg.\nThe entrance of Public Utility\nHolding Corporation into Luxem\nbourg marks the third acquisition\nannounced within a week in Eu\nropean public utility fields, follow\ning closely the acquisition by the\ncorporation of a large minority\ninterest in L\u2019Union Electrique\nRurale and the arrangements for\njoint purchase with the Deutsche\nBank of Berlin of a half interest\nin the equity of Westphalia United\nElectric Power Corporation of Ger\nmany.\nConsolidation\nThis latest acquisition repre\nsents a further alignment of Pub\nlic Utility Holding Corporation\nwith the Mahieu-Lousteau inter\nests, which are also Identified with\nL\u2019Union Electrique Rurale, and in\neach instance the holdings of the\nAmerican and French interests\nconstitute control of these prop\nerties., Senator Albert Mahieu, of\nFrance is president of the Luxem\nbourg company.\nIt is pointed out by Burroughs\nthat the entrance of Public Util\nity Holding into Luxembourg is in\nline with the previously announced\npolicy of the corporation to secure\na substantial minority stock in\nterest in utility properties where\nsuch interests along with those\nof associates give a combined\ncontrol. As in the case of L\u2019Un\nion Electrique Rurale the holdings\nof both Public Utility Holding\nCorporation and the associated\nFrench interests will be blocked\nand voted as a unit.\nServes Entire Duchy\nThe Compagnie Grand d\u2019Elect\nricite de Luxembourg will serve\npractically the entire Duchy with\nelectrical energy with the excep\ntion of some small localities which\ndraw from existing independent\nplants. The company is a large\npurchaser of current from the\nexpensive steel and other indus\ntrial works of Luxembourg. The\nDuchy, with a population of ap\nproximately 285.000, is the heart\nof one of the leading coal and\niron basins of Europe. The ma\njority of manufacturing and min\ning concerns are located in the\nsouthern portion of the state,\nwhile the northern part of the\ncountry is devoted mainly to agri\nculture. The total iron and steel\nproduction of the Duchy amounts\nto 70 per cent of the Belgian total\nand 11 per cent of Germany\u2019s\noutput. The government of the\nDuchy is closely connected with\nthe development of its industry\nand commerce, including the de\nvelopment of electrical facilities.\nRecent reports indicate that there\nis no unemployment in the Duchy,\nbut that on the contrary the em\nployment of foreign labor is sig\nnificant of its economic prosper\nity.\nThe management of the Luxem\nbourg company is in the hands of\na board of directors which is\nlimited to not more than 12\nAT YOUR THEATER TONIGHT I\nOFFICIAL PROGRAMS of Theater Member* of the\nMotion Picture Theater Owner* of District of Columbia\nFOX F at Fourteenth\nGeorpe O'Brien and Helen Chandler\nIn.' ROIGH ROMANCE\u201d\nStare\u2014Fanchon and Marco\n\u201cInternational Idea\u201d\nSam .lack Kaofmnn. l*re\u00abldlnr\nLeun Brunllofr mid Fox Orchestra\nFO\\ MOVIETONE NEWS\n(PALACE F St at 13th\nI Lillian Gifih In \"One Romantic\nOlNl<ht. H Sfu<c \u2014Dave Schooler in\nKevue \u2014\u2022\u2022Steel Blue*.\u2019\u2019 Dick\nEl albert\u2014\u2022\u2022Ontanloiriie Creation\u201d\nHearst Metrotone News\nj Palace Orchestra\nW COLUMBIA\u2014 FStat 12th\n'THE BIG HOUSE.\" with ChMtef\n8 Morri* and Leila B.ram*\nLaurel A Hardy tn *BeJow Zero**\nHearst Metrotone New*\nColumbia Orche*tra\nREPUBLIC 0 8t Hth\nnbrUDblU Phone North ISM\nJanet Gaynor and Charles Farrell\nin \u201cHIGH SOCIETY BLUES\u2019* 7\nJ*|LINCOLN nigl t N w\nI Tom Moore and Blanche Sweet\nIn \u201cWOMAN RACKET\u201d\nUnderworld Drama\nH BOOKER T \u2014.SJfa.r\"\nT Lawrence Gray\u2014Helen Johnson\n-g \u201cCHILDREN OF PLEABUKE\u201d\nyj ROSALIA Bt B w\nJame* Murray\u2014\u201c The Hldeoat\u201d\nBROADWAY ,ft,^VVr w 7\n8 HARRY RICHMAN I\n\"PUTTIN' ON THE RITZ\u201d\nVacation\n\u25a0Eft?;;:#\nbi\na\n\nJH\n\u2014Time* Staff Photo\nCLAUD H. WOODWARD\nPRESIDENT OF the Mt. Ver\nnon Savings Bank who is at\nOld Orchard. Me., on vacation.\nThe banking executive will\nspend a month in the resort\nbefore returning to his desk.\nraLTTEB\nn.000.D00\nEarnings of General Realty and\nUtilities Corporation before taxes\nfor five months ended May 31,\nwere slightly in excess of $2,-\n000.000. This figure does not in\nclude determined but unrealized\nprofits which will come into in\ncome in the second half of 1930.\nBased upon business which\nGeneral Realty has on its books\nand unrealized profits to be\ntaken later. Louis W. Abrons.\npresident, states that second-half\nearnings will exceed those of the\nfirst half and net profits for\nthe full year will be substan\ntially in excess of 1929 when net\nincome for 11 months of opera\ntions ended December 31 last\nwas $3,480,611. General Realty\nalso has on its books business\nconsummated this year, income\nfrom which will not be received\nuntil 1931 or 1932.\n\u201cConditions in the building\nindustry are o n a healthy\nbasis,\u201d says Mr. Abrons, \"and\nit is notable that while security\nmarkets have shown a shrink\nage of values as compared with\nlast year, good real estate\nbought at the same time has\nbeen sold at very much higher\nprices.\u201d\nGeneral Realty has been con\nspicuously active in real estate\nthis spring in the East End Ave\nnue district and in downtown\nNew York. Company also ac\nquired the Stem Brothers Build\ning on Forty-second Street be\ntween Fifth and Sixth avenues.\nThis property is valued at more\nthan $6,000,000.\nAcceptance Rate at\nBoston Is Reduced\nBOSTOI\u2019 July 3.\u2014Federal re\nserve bank of Boston has reduced\nits acceptance buying rate for 1\nto 45 days to 1% per cent. Other\nrates remain at 2 per cent for\n46 to 90 days, 2\u2019/ 8 per cent for\n91 to 120 days and 2% per cent\nfor 121 to 180 days\nWARNER BROS. THEATERS\nAMBASSABOR \u2018\"S;.' ri\u2122\nRIN TIN TIN\nin \"ROUGH WATERS\"\nVltaphonft Variety and Comedy\nAPOLLO\nRIN TIN TIN\nin \u201cROUGH WATERS\u201d\nComedy and Vltaphone Variety\nAVAI Oil Connecticat Ate. and\nMIMbUM McKinley St. D. C.\nJACK MULHALL\nin \"IN THE NEXT ROOM\"\nand Comedy\nAVENUE GRAND\nJACK MULHALL\nin \"IN THE NEXT ROOM\"\nVltaphone Variety and Comedy\nPmTRAI Ninth St. Between\n\u00dcbN 111 Mb d and E Sta.\nBARBARA KENT\nin \u201cDUMBELLB IN ERMINE\u201d\nVltaphone Variety and Comedy\nCOLONY Farraant St. I\nBENNY RUBIN\nin \"SUNNY SKIKS\"\nVltaphone Variety and Comedy\nTA If Alli Eonrth and Batternat.\nI MnUHIM Takoma I\u2019ark. D, C.\nTalking Pictnrea at Their Beet\n\u201cThe Loet Zeppelin\u201d and Hoot Gibson\nIn \"Conrtlnt Wildcat*\u201d\nUTILITY SHARES\n.ARE SOLD\nEATDN-OTIS\n'Profits Between $15,000,000\nand $20,000,000 During\nSecond Quarter Reported\nSale by the Eaton-Otis interests\nof large holdings in public utility\ncompanies will be revealed in the\nmid-year statement of Continental\nShares, an Investment trust con\ntrolled by this group, according\nto a semiofficial announcement\nmade yesterday. This company is\nunderstood to have realized\nprofits of from >15.000,000 to\n120,000,000 during the second\nquarter from the sale of utility\nstocks. Although It is not known\nwhat securities were sold, the\nprincipal utility holdings of this\ncompany, according to its last\npublished portfolio, were Com\nv monwealth Edison, Peoples Gas\nLight Coke, Lehigh Coal\nNavigation, Brooklyn Union Gas,\nInternational Paper Power and\nUnited light Power.\nThe securities disposed of, it is\nunderstood, were largely or en\ntirely from the public utility\ngroup, in which investments, on\nthe basis of market value, totaled\n$61,091,704 as of March 31, the\ndate of the most recent published\nstatement. The outstanding indi\nvidual holdings, in point of value\nat that time were as follow*.\nC'monwealth Edison 88,435 *19,141.134\nLehigh Coal A N\u00abv. 4<13.053 19.447,3*7\nPeoples Gas 45.30* 14,224,20*\nCliffs Corp 245,142 33.929,598\nRepublic Steel \u202211.182,841\nI \u2018Combined values of holdings in\nBourne-Fuller, Central Alloy Steel and\nDonner.\nBecause of its position in the\niron ore and steel industries, it is\nunderstood that Continental\nShares\u2019 holdings in Cliffs Corpor\nation and the Republic Steel Cor\nporation remain undisturbed.\nAssets of Continental Shares,\nInc., on March 31. aggregated\n$130,664,572, while the correspond\ning figure at this time is prob\nably about $10,000,000 greater.\nWhere cash holdings three\nmonths ago .were less than\n$1,750,000 they are understood to\nj be four times that amount now.\nWestinghouse Forms\nNew X-Ray Company\nThe formation of the Westing\nhouse X-ray Company, Inc-,\nmarks the entrance of the West\ninghouse Electric and Manufac\nturing Company into the field of\nx-ray and electro-medical appara\ntus manufacture and the devel\nopment and further application\nof these instruments as machines\nto prolong life.\nThe new company, incorporated\nin Delaware, on June 25, has an\ninitial capitalization of $2,000,000.\n$33,600,1)00 CMt>n\nBanks by Treasury\nUnited States Treasury has\ncalled for repayment by depos\nitary institutions in Second Fed\neral Reserve District on July 5,\nof $12,568,900, representing 12 Va\nper cent of the combined amounts\nplaced on deposit for account of\ncertificate of indebtedness issue\ndated June 16. The call for en\ntire country is $33,695,500. After\nthis withdrawal there will remain\non deposit in thr district $87,-\n982,600.\nFADI E Thirteenth Street\nUtnLt Below V Street\nFAY WRAY and RICHARD ARLEN\nIn \u2019THE BORDER LEGION\u201d\nAdded Short Subjects\nIIMIF C Street\nnum*. Northeast\nRICHARD ARLEN in \"THR LIGHT\nOF WESTERN STARS.\u201d Vitaphone\nVariety and Serial. \u2018The Jade Box\u2019 No. 4\nMETROPOLITAN\nVIVIENNE SEGAL and WALTER\nWOOLF in GOLDEN DAWN\u201d\nAdded Short Subject*\nSAVOY 14th Colombia Rd.\nNorthwest\nKEN MAT N ARD\nin \"MOUNTAIN JUSTICE\u201d\nand Comedy\nTIVOLI Northwest\nDOROTHY MACKAILL\nin \u2019THE FLIRTING WIDOW\u201d\nand Vitaphone Variety\nYORK Georgia Avenue and\nUnit Quebec Street\nW I L L T A M BOYD\nin \"OFFICER O\u2019BRIKN\"\nand Comedy\nR-K-0 KEITHS\nRICHARD DIX MART LAWLOR\ntn \"SHOOTIN\u201d OTATGHT\"\nCanal Added Attractions\n15","height":"30430","width":"24426"}}
